laws for the sake of all Namibians, stressed Mbumba.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\">Speaker of the National Assembly, Peter Katjavivi thanked members of the 7th Parliament for their commitment for putting in extra hours to complete discussions on pending bills and other items on the order paper and making sure that other tasks on the order paper are finalized.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\">Out-going leader of the Official opposition party, McHenry Venaani commended Mbumba for providing leadership and direction to the nation during a difficult period.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a\">\n<div dir=\"auto\">President Mbumba will hand over power to President-elect Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah on Friday.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>FAREWELL Story By: Noreen Sitali As the 7th Parliament prepares to conclude its term on the 19th of March 2025, paving the way for the swearing-in ceremony for members of the 8th Parliament and the election of the Speaker and Deputy Speaker on the 20th of March, ahead of the transition, President Nangolo Mbumba delivered&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":16,"featured_media":18217,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[159,39],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-18214","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-home-page-slider","category-news","category-159","category-39","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/18214","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":tr